{"lemma":"فَوْقَ","slug":"فَوْقَ","root":"ف.#.ق","root_slug":"ف-_-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-_-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَوْقَ","root":"فوق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":41},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adv","prep"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34848","n34849"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adv","gloss":"above"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"above, on top of"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"more than, over","examples":[{"text":"كَانُوا فَوْقَ ٱلْعِشْرِينَ","english":"They were more than twenty"},{"text":"فَإِنْ كُنَّ نِسَاءً فَوْقَ ٱثْنَتَيْنِ فَلَهُنَّ ثُلُثَا مَا تَرَكَ"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"more important than"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Originally a case form of a defective noun فَوْق (fawq, “location that is above”); see the usage note. From the root ف و ق (f w q)."},"ipa":["/faw.qu/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34848","headword_ar":"فَوْق","root":"fwq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHot","text_ar":"تَحْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) [primarily signifying The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"location that is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and is an adv. n. (Mgh, Msb, K) of place; (Mgh, Msb;) and a simple noun, indecl., [with dammeh for its termination, when the noun to which it should be prefixed is suppressed, and the meaning of this is intended to be understood, but not the word itself;] but when it is prefixed to another noun [which is either expressed or itself (and not merely its meaning) meant to be understood, and when the noun to which it should be prefixed is suppressed and neither this nor its meaning is meant to be understood,] it is declinable. (K. [For the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuwnu A@somFA waZarofFA maboniY~N","text_ar":"يَكُونُ ا@سْمًا وَظَرْفًا مَبْنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reading of the K in the TA and CK, my MS. copy of the K (which I follow in this case) has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ykwn ZrfA wAsmA mbny~A","text_ar":"يكون ظرفا واسما مبنيّا"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN fawoqa Als~aToHi","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ فَوْقَ السَّطْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, the house-top"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEimaAmapu","text_ar":"العِمَامَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoqa Alr~aA^osi","text_ar":"فَوْقَ الرَّاْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The turban is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TafaA fawoqa AlmaA='i","text_ar":"طَفَا فَوْقَ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It floated upon the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S &c. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tfw","text_ar":"طفو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Ks has mentioned the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afawoqa tanaAmu A^amo A^asofala","text_ar":"اَفَوْقَ تَنَامُ اَمْ اَسْفَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dost thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wilt thou, sleep in the part that is above"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the house &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or in the part that is below?"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the upper part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the lower part?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] with fet-h, as suppressing the noun to which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwq","text_ar":"فوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [meant to be understood as] prefixed. (TA.) Lth says that he who uses it as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sifap","text_ar":"صِفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by which (like other old writers) he means an adv. n. of place] should use the accus. case, as when one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabodu A@ll~`hi fawoqa","text_ar":"عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ فَوْقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodK","text_ar":"زَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"'Abd-Allah is above Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but if you make it simply a noun, you use the nom. case, and say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoquhu raA^osuhu","text_ar":"فَوْقُهُ رَاْسُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His superior"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part is his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for in this instance it is the head itself, and you make each to be governed in the nom. case by the other. (TA.) In the saying in the Kur [xvi. 28],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxar~a Ealayohimu A@ls~aqofu mino fawoqihimo","text_ar":"فَخَرَّ عَلَيْهِمُ ا@لسَّقْفُ مِنْ فَوْقِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the roof fell on them from above them"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the utility of the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fwqhm","text_ar":"من فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is hardly apparent,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2462},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elyhm","text_ar":"عليهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes serves in its stead: but IJ says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fwqhm","text_ar":"من فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"may here have a useful office; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in relation to deeds [or events] that are difficult, and deemed onerous; [for instance,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado sironaA Ea$orFA","text_ar":"قَدْ سِرْنَا عَشْرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabaqiyato EalayonaA layolataAni","text_ar":"وَبَقِيَتْ عَلَيْنَا لَيْلَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have journeyed ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"nights"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the journeys"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two nights have remained"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though incumbent"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; &c.; so that if it were said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fxr~ Elyhm Alsqf","text_ar":"فخرّ عليهم السقف"},{"kind":"text","text":"without the adding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn fwqhm","text_ar":"من فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":", it might be supposed to be like the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohimo daAruhumo qado xaribato","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمْ دَارُهُمْ قَدْ خَرِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their abode had become in a state of ruin"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a punishment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but when He [referring to God] says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwqhm","text_ar":"فوقهم"},{"kind":"text","text":", that meaning which was supposable ceases to be so; and the meaning becomes this, that it [the roof] fell when they were beneath it. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*o jaAw^uwkumo mino fawoqikumo wamino A^asofala minokumo","text_ar":"اـِذْ جَاوُوكُمْ مِنْ فَوْقِكُمْ وَمِنْ اَسْفَلَ مِنْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When they came to you from above you and from below you"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in the Kur [xxxiii. 10], relates to Benoo- Kureydhah, who came to them from above them; and to Kureysh and Ghatafán, who came from the district of Mekkeh, from below them. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iyna A@t~aquwA fawoqahumo yawoma A@loqiyaAmapi","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِينَ ا@تَّقُوا فَوْقَهُمْ يَوْمَ ا@لْقِيَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [ii. 208], means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"But those who have been careful of their religious duties"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be above them in station"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the day of resurrection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) And one says, [agreeably with what has been stated in the first sentence of this paragraph,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu mino fawoqu","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ مِنْ فَوْقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu mino fawoqK","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ مِنْ فَوْقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overpowered him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAhu mn","text_ar":"اَتَاهُ من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fwq","text_ar":"فوق"},{"kind":"text","text":", as expl. in the Ham p. 128. i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaharahu","text_ar":"قَهَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, his adversary; and so a hawk, his pr? or quarry. (M and K in an expl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adal~a Ealayoh","text_ar":"اَدَلَّ عَلَيْه"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dl","text_ar":"دل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And [in a similar manner]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoq","text_ar":"فَوْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is metaphorically used as denoting excess, (Mgh, Msb.) and excellence: (Msb:) thus one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEa$arapu fawoqa","text_ar":"العَشَرَةُ فَوْقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~isoEapi","text_ar":"التِّسْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ten is above nine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten exceeds nine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA fawoqa","text_ar":"هٰذَا فَوْقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is above,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superior to, that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is more excellent than that;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and hence, (Mgh, Msb,) in the Kur iii. 24], (S, O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEuwDapF famaA fawoqahaA","text_ar":"بَعُوضَةً فَمَا فَوْقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gnat and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what exceeds it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in smallness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in largeness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is smaller than it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is larger than it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the latter being meant the fly [mentioned in the Kur xxii. 72] and the spider [mentioned in xxix. 40], (Fr, S, O,) and the phrase as expl. in the former sense being like the reply to him who says “ Such a one is small ”"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*`lika wafawoqa","text_ar":"ذٰلِكَ وَفَوْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And smaller than that:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, O:) hence also, in the Kur iii. 12],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_ino kun~a nisaA='F fawoqa A@vonatayoni","text_ar":"فَاـِنْ كُنَّ نِسَا=ءً فَوْقَ ا@ثْنَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb) i. e. (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And if they are women,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","K","S","O","AO","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n34849","headword_ar":"فُوقٌ","root":"fwq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the arrow,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the place of the bow-string;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"notch"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof;] (S, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqapN","text_ar":"فُوقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K;) the former is masc., and also, like the latter, fem. (IAmb, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuwqaAni","text_ar":"الفُوقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanamataAni","text_ar":"زَنَمَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two cusps of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwq","text_ar":"فُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between which is put the bow string"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (O, K;) thus these are termed by the tribe of Hudheyl; but a poet who has used the dual form is said by AO to has mead thereby a single"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwq","text_ar":"فُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) the pl. [of mult.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwaqN","text_ar":"فُوَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afowaAqN","text_ar":"اَفْوَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb, K;) or, accord. to ISk, these are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqapN","text_ar":"فُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufFA","text_ar":"قُفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is a pl., formed by transposition; [see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroquwbN","text_ar":"عُرْقُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (K, TA;) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqowapN","text_ar":"فُقْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuqFA","text_ar":"فُقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqapN","text_ar":"فُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwaqN","text_ar":"فُوَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomN *uw fuwqK","text_ar":"سَهْمٌ ذُو فُوقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"rendered complete by its"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwq","text_ar":"فُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aA","text_ar":"ذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqK","text_ar":"فُوقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in a trad. [as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A complete share;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomN","text_ar":"سَهْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ a share ” as well as “ an arrow ”]. (A'Obeyd, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAhumo","text_ar":"اَعْلَاهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqFA","text_ar":"فُوقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they, of them, haring the largest share of religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a metaphorical phrase, from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwq","text_ar":"فُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the arrow. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqobilo EalaY fuwqi nabolika","text_ar":"اَقْبِلْ عَلَى فُوقِ نَبْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or, app.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwaqi nabolika","text_ar":"فُوَقِ نَبْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabolN","text_ar":"نَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a coll. n., meaning “ arrows, ” or “ Arabian arrows, ”] meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Betake thyself to thy affair, and that which concerns thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramayonaA fuwqFA","text_ar":"رَمَيْنَا فُوقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqFA waAHidFA","text_ar":"فُوقًا وَاحِدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ri$oqFA","text_ar":"رِشْقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We shot in one direction;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we shot one bout, in one direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (O, K, TA.) ―         -b5-  [Hence, app.,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAn fulaAnN liA^aw~ali fuwqi","text_ar":"كان فُلَانٌ لِاَوَّلِ فُوقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  Such a one was [for the first discharge from the bow, i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first shot and dying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b6-  And [hence, perhaps.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqN","text_ar":"فُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwaqN","text_ar":"فُوَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA) One says to a man when he enters upon a mode, or manner, of speech,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa*o fiY fuwqi A^aHosana","text_ar":"خَذْ فِى فُوقِ اَحْسَنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Enter upon a mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of speech better than it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b7-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first way"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O K, TA.) ―         -b8-  Hence. app., [they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirojaEo A_in $i}ota fiY fuwqK","text_ar":"اِرْجَعْ اـِن شِئْتَ فِى فُوقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Return thou, if thou wilt, to the state of close,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loving, communion in which we were."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, Z, O,TA.) -b8- And the Arabs say, in imprecating,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqihi laA rajEa fulaAnN A_ilaY","text_ar":"فُوقِهِ لَا رَجعَ فُلَانٌ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"i.e.(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May such a one die:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says AA; and he cites the following verse of El-'Uleykim El-Kindee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"maA baAlu EirosiY $ariqato biriyqihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        vum~ata laA yarojiEo lahaA mino fuwqihaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is the case of my wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she is choked by her spittle? Then,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"afterward,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(her spittle)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not return to its channel"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her throat, the way whence it came"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that she may be suffocated). (O.) ―         -b9-  And one says (O, K) or a man when he has gone away, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@rotad~a EalaY fuwqihi","text_ar":"ا@رْتَدَّ عَلَى فُوقِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  He went away and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not return"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the place whence he departed"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (O, K) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqN","text_ar":"فُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies, (O, K.) accord. to Ibn-'Abbád, (O, TA.) (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vulva of a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K. TA) but As says that this is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [it is, however, also said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwqu Alr~aHimi","text_ar":"فُوقُ الرَّحِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rima of the vulva,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by way of comparison [to the notch of the arrow]. (TA, in the supplement to this art.) ―         -b11-  [And app. (assumed tropical:) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"front edge of the lobe of the ear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 1 in art"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hrm","text_ar":"حرم"},{"kind":"text","text":", when it is mentioned in such a manner as seems to preclude its being a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawf","text_ar":"قَوف"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b12-  And (as Ibn-'Abbád says, O) (assumed tropical:) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of opening"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforaj","text_ar":"مَفْرَج"},{"kind":"text","text":", O. TA, in the K erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxoraj","text_ar":"مَخْرَج"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawobap,","text_ar":"جَوْبَة,"},{"kind":"text","text":"O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (as some say, O) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of the tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) ―         -b13-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost part of the penis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(En-Nadr, O, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the glans thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  And, accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird;"},{"kind":"text","text":"mean ing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain aquatic bird:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is correctly ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwqN","text_ar":"قُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with two káfs. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAqN","text_ar":"فَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one."}],"source_refs":["IAmb","Msb","O","K","TA","A"]}]}}